[Black "2.b3 Ne7"]
[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5
{ Let's have a quick look at very, very rare second moves. None of them is threatening at all, and the best White could hope it to transpose into one of the previous chapters. }
2. b3 Ne7
{ I'm quite happy with this novelty!   Of course, the goal is the same as  2...Nf6  ,  playing  3.--  d5  . But here, the knight is better placed on e7, let's see why! }
3. Bb2 Nbc6 4. Nf3 d5
{ Gambitting the e5-pawn, the following lines will clearly show that the knight is much better placed on e7! }
5. Nxe5 Nxe5 6. Bxe5 d4 { It is already a disaster for White. } 7. e3
{ White tries to unblock the center, but now the knight on e7 will prove very useful. }
7... Nc6 8. Bg3 h5 9. h4 Qf6
{ Would be even worse, White having problems with his a1-rook already, while: }
10. Qf3 Qg6 { Will soon be met by ...Bg4/...Bf5 or/and ...Nb4. } *

