[Result "*"]

1. c4 e5 2. g3 Nf6 3. Nc3 c6 4. d4 exd4
{ Although  4...e4  is playable here too, with the knight on c3 @@StartBracket@@instead of Bg2@@EndBracket@@ I would advice to capture on d4, for a reason I've explained earlier: in isolated pawn positions, ...Nc6 and ...d4 will be much more disturbing with a white knight on c3, not talking about the delayed development of the white kingside. }
5. Qxd4 d5 6. Nf3 Na6
{ Instead,  6...Be6  is fully playable, but this is my favourite. } 7. Bg2
{ 7.cxd5?!  Nb4  threatening ...Nc2+ and followed by ...Nbxd5 is more than fine for Black. }
7... Bc5
{ My advice. If White doesn't give a check on e5, this is just a free tempo! }
8. Qh4 O-O 9. O-O
{ 9.Bg5  Be7  10.cxd5  h6  is even easier for Black - as the vis-à-vis Be7/Qh4 definitely doesn't help White. }
9... dxc4 10. Qxc4 Be6
{ Followed by either ...Nd5, ... h6, ...Bb6, ...Re8, is just entirely fine for Black. }
