9... c6
{ Black wants to take control of the center, and possibly one day break it with ...d5 or even ...b5.   9...a5!?  in order to ensure the dark-squared bishop can never be exchanged after  10.a3  Bc5  is also highly interesting, according to the engine, and is a novelty.  However, I believe it makes even more sense to immediately take control of the center with @@StartFEN@@r2qk2r/ppp2ppp/3p1n2/4p3/1bPnP3/2NP2PP/PP3P2/R1BQKB1R b KQkq - 2 9@@EndFEN@@  9...c6  the main recommendation in the course. }
