Bf5 { Here White needs to be very careful! } 14. Rfc1
{ A natural move that falls into a beautiful trick.   The capture:  14.Qxb7  Rb8  15.Qxa7  Rxb2  would be highly unpleasant for White, the e2-pawn being hanging, a2 being poetically lost  (... Qa8)  and still very passive pieces.   14.f3  Re8  Black has absolutely nothing to worry about and enjoys a slight advantage, for the simple reasons that he has more space and that White's pieces on the kingside will need a lot of time to become active if they ever do.   Black has easy play ahead with ...Qd7/...Qb6, ...Rac8, and White can basically only hope that his passive kingside pieces won't be too much of a drama. }
