1. c4 e5 2. d3
{ There are different possibilities against 2.d3, though this move hides much more venom than you may think at first.   As a matter of consistency, and also because I think it's the best line, I'll suggest playing a reversed Open Sicilian here as well. }
2... Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. a3 d5 5. cxd5 Nxd5
{ Here we have a reversed Najdorf Sicilian. } 6. e3
{ This is easier to meet: it is a slow move, which means that the extra tempo White got in a reversed Sicilian will matter less.   Here I'm going to suggest a setup I believe is very easy to handle as Black. }
6... Bd6 7. Nc3 Nxc3 8. bxc3 O-O 9. Be2 Qe7
{ Followed by ...b6, ...Bb7, ...Rad8, is just an easy game for Black. } *

