1. c4 e5 2. e3 Nf6 3. a3 d5 4. cxd5 Nxd5
{ Has no independent value: Black hasn't even played ...Nc6 so he doesn't even have to worry about Bb5. Next could be ...Bd6, or even ...g6. }
5. Nc3 Nxc3 { As usual, we answer 5.Nc3 with 5...Nxc3. } 6. bxc3 Bd6 7. d4 O-O
{ With a perfectly fine position - the knight still standing on b8 even surely granting Black a small advantage as he's going to push ...c5 very soon, if not next. }
